Healthcare providers should show empathy verbally to their patients, communicating their understanding of patients' feelings and emotions; Healthcare providers should offer reassurance and empathy during consultation, to try to alleviate patients' anxiety and help them feel better; Healthcare providers should show care and concern about patients as human beings, not as a bundle of symptoms or medical problems; Healthcare providers should know patients' personal, familial, social, and cultural backgrounds in order to treat patients' illness;  Healthcare providers should offer empathetic or supportive comments to establish a friendly medical relationship; Healthcare providers should respond with empathy to patients' concerns; Healthcare providers should not talk about only the medical aspects of patients' illnesses, without caring about their feelings.

After consultation, healthcare providers should give patients all test results, even if they show no abnormalities; Healthcare providers should be available to answer patients' medical questions; Healthcare providers should give a complete explanation of patients' medical symptoms and treatments, including possible side-effects, if any;  Healthcare providers should check patients' understanding of what they are saying and allow correction of misunderstandings;  Healthcare providers should not talk down to patients; they should communicate with their patients as equals;  Healthcare providers should never expose patients to unnecessary risk.

Healthcare providers should avoid disturbances during consultation from telephone calls, visitors; During consultation, healthcare providers should maintain eye contact with patients, revealing interest and sincerity in what patients are saying;  Healthcare providers should show warmth to their patients;  Healthcare providers should not be too businesslike and impersonal toward patients; Healthcare providers should not talk about patients in front of them, as if they were not there;  During consultation, healthcare providers should maintain a friendly and respectful manner, responding with appropriate smiles and nods; In addition to inquiring about patients' illnesses, healthcare providers should ask about their general well-being.

Healthcare providers should make medical decisions taking patients' preferences or opinions into accounts and reach a final agreement with their patients; Healthcare providers should encourage patients to talk about personal concerns related to their medical symptoms; Healthcare providers should encourage patients to give their opinions about their medical treatments and how they prefer to be treated; Healthcare providers should negotiate with patients to derive a mutually agreeable treatment plan; Healthcare providers should treat patients as partners; Healthcare providers should !,>ive patients the opportunity to offer their opinions about the test(s) or treatment( s) that healthcare providers recommend.
